metadata.name: We Are Here
metadata.description:
It was not long ago that barter was the main way to exchange goods and services. 

Over time, the desire for a more efficient means led to the use of gold as a medium of exchange, and its lustrous shine soon became a symbol of wealth and power.

For the sake of convenience, precious coins were adopted in the ancient world and eventually, paper money paved the way for international commerce.

We Are Here #1 is a moment in time before we completely transcend the systems of monetary exchange we have collectively built and move on to a new programmable frontier.

It is an urgent immutable remark.
